  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6600 sitting between the major negative gamma wall at 6590 (-25.7B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+33.6B), dealers are currently in a neutral hedging posture but primed for significant flow once we break either level. The PIN regime and massive GEX surge suggest dealers will aggressively sell any push above 6605 and buy heavily on any break below 6590, creating a tight 15-point range with explosive potential outside these bounds. Key inflection points are the 6590 support (where dealer buying accelerates) and 6629 flip strike (where regime changes to negative gamma if breached).\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect choppy action locked between 6590-6605 with big moves if either level breaks.",
